:INFO
Preparing Your Specimens
Collect plants in the morning after dew has dried. Choose specimens that represent the \
plant fully: include leaves, stem, and ideally a flower or seed head. Gently remove \
excess bulk from thick stems or compound leaves. Arrange the specimen on blotting

