:INFO
Mounting and Labeling
Attach dried specimens to acid-free paper using small strips of linen tape or a thin \
bead of PVA glue applied with a toothpick. Never use pressure-sensitive tapes. Label \
each specimen with the common name, scientific name if known, collection location,

:QUOTE
A pressed flower is a small act of preservation. Every one you mount is a record \
that something beautiful existed in a specific place on a specific day.
